=== Plugin name fields per construct ===
[skill-example] plugin.json name = "skill-example"
[command-example] plugin.json name = "command-example"
[agent-example] plugin.json name = "agent-example"
[mcp-example] plugin.json name = "mcp-example"
[hook-example] plugin.json name = "hook-example"

=== Per-construct content files ===
--- skill-example: SKILL.md frontmatter (name field) ---
---
name: example-skill
description: Reference example. Echoes back a formatted lab-notebook-style status message. Shows how to write a SKILL.md with frontmatter, allowed-tools, and argument handling.
argument-hint: "[topic]"
allowed-tools:
  - Bash
  - Read
---

--- command-example: commands/example-command.md ---
example-command.md
---
description: Reference example slash command. Prints a formatted lab-notebook header.
---

--- agent-example: agents/notebook-reviewer.md ---
notebook-reviewer.md
---
name: notebook-reviewer
description: Reviews a lab notebook entry as a skeptical peer reviewer. Use when the user has drafted a notebook entry and wants a critical second opinion before publishing.
tools: Read, Grep, Glob
---

--- mcp-example: mcp-config.json mcpServers keys ---
[
  "example-fetch"
]

